article.headline: Pennsylvania 104, Harvard 69
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Jeff Schiffner had 24 points and Adam Chubb added 17 as hot-shooting Penn defeated Harvard 104-69 Friday night. Tim Begley had 12 points and tied his career high with nine assists for the Quakers (8-8, 1-2 Ivy), while Ibby Jaaber added 13 points. Penn hit on 37 of 56 shots in the game (66 percent) in recording its highest point total since a 114-73 win over Haverford in 1993. Jason Norman had 12 points and Matt Stehle 11 for Harvard (2-16, 1-4), while Graham Beatty and Jim Goffredo each had 10. Harvard stayed close for the first five-and-a-half minutes, trailing 15-13 before the Quakers went on a 25-7 run to lead 40-20 with 5:45 left in the first half. After two Harvard field goals, Penn ran off the final 15 points of the half to lead 55-24. Paced by Schiffner's 18 points, the Quakers made 22 of 30 shots in the first 20 minutes, while Harvard was 10 for 26 and committed 11 turnovers. Three-point shots by Schiffner and Begley sparked a 16-3 spurt midway through the second half, giving Penn its largest lead at 86-41 with 9:21 left in the game.
